{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A plugin whose manifest is missing a required field is rejected before any code from that plugin is executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Unit -> Integration proof: the failure is at a module handoff between manifest validation and plugin execution gating (validator must block importer/hook runner). A pure validator unit test can pass while loader still imports plugin code. Rejected higher levels: the behavior text only requires rejection/execution ordering inside the loader process; it does not require real subprocess, network, OS event semantics, or any AI output.","test_description":"Create a temp plugin directory with one plugin whose manifest.json omits a required field and an entry module that writes a side-effect marker when executed. Run the real loader against the directory and assert: (1) validation error is reported for that plugin, (2) side-effect marker was never produced, (3) plugin onLoad was never called.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When plugin A declares a dependency on plugin B, plugin B's onLoad hook is called before plugin A's.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Unit -> Integration proof: failure appears when dependency resolver output is handed to lifecycle executor; either module can be correct alone but wrong together. Rejected higher levels: behavior text is about in-process ordering of hooks, with no requirement for subprocess/real network/OS-specific primitives, and no model output dependency.","test_description":"Set up two real plugin packages in a temp directory: A depends on B. Each onLoad appends its name to a shared in-memory log/file. Run loader and assert log order is [\"B\",\"A\"].","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When two plugins each declare a dependency on the other, the loader reports the cycle and loads neither.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Unit -> Integration proof: cycle detection must propagate to load-prevention logic; bug can occur at resolver->executor interface (cycle detected but still loaded, or vice versa). Rejected higher levels: behavior text only concerns dependency graph/reporting and load suppression in the loader, not real OS/network/subprocess behavior and not AI-driven correctness.","test_description":"Create plugins A and B where A depends on B and B depends on A. Run loader and assert: (1) cycle error/report includes A<->B, (2) neither entry module executes, (3) neither onLoad runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A plugin's onLoad hook is only invoked after the plugin's entry module has been imported and executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Unit -> Integration proof: this is an importer->lifecycle handoff ordering guarantee; testing one function alone cannot catch misordered orchestration. Rejected higher level (System): behavior text says imported/executed before onLoad, which can be validated in-process with real module import in the same runtime; no subprocess, external API, or OS event dependency is required. No AI dependency, so not Agentic/Workflow.","test_description":"Create a plugin whose entry module sets a module-level flag/side effect during import, and whose onLoad asserts that flag is already set (or records observed state). Run loader and assert onLoad sees post-import state; fail if onLoad ran before import execution.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.17,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5